CUE CARDS - online help


"Cue Cards" is a unque and extremely useful wayof providing help to
the users as when and when they actually need it.

CueCards->Help Mode: If this is turned on, subsequent actions by the
user do not perform the actual operation, but bring up online help on
that feature instead. This is an excellent way to get answers for
"What does that do? And this one?"

CueCards->On-line Tutorial This brings up an online tutorial. If you
are running Movieola for the first time, this comes up automatically.
It is strongly recommended that you go through the tutorial before
starting to use the program seriously.

CueCards->On Context This brings up a cue card on whatever you are
doing currently. If you keep the cue card window up, it constantly
updates to give you help on whatever you are doing currently. As a
beginner, you will find the context-sensitive help invaluable. More
experienced users can also use this as a reference.

CueCards->On Topic This brings up a list of topics, that you can get
help on.

CueCards->On Cue Cards This brings up this information.

CueCards->On Product Philosophy This brings up a little essay on
Movieola, its design philosphy, and its user focus.

CueCards->On Movieola This brings up information about Radiance
Software and how to call customer support.
